  sodium: 4.6 g
  serving size: 554
cuisine: Mexican
author: Anushka Magan
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/sticky-glazed-halloumi-and-chipotle-pilaf-65b9025cd1da3988cdd8dbc1
time required: 45 minutes
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1%unit}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a deep #saucepan{} (with a #tight-fitting lid{}) on medium
heat.

Once hot, add the onion, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and fry, stirring
occasionally, until golden and soft, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain the @halloumi{225%grams}, then cut it into 2cm chunks. Place
them into a small #bowl{} of cold water and leave to soak.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated with a garlic press).

Once the onion is golden, stir in the @cider vinegar{15%milliliter} and @sugar{½%tsp}
and allow the vinegar to evaporate, ~{1%minute}.

Stir the garlic into the onions and fry for ~{1%minute}, then add the
@basmati rice{150%grams} and stir until coated, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @vegetable stock paste{15%grams} and @water for the rice{300%milliliter}
and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover
with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still
covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} (the rice will continue
to cook in its own steam).

Once the rice is off the heat and steaming, remove the halloumi from the water.
Pop onto a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{} and pat dry. Sprinkle over the
@lemon & herb seasoning{1%sachet} and season with pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the halloumi and fry until golden, ~{2-3%minutes} each side.

Add the @honey{1%tbsp} and turn the halloumi so it's nicely glazed, then
remove from the heat. Cover to keep warm.

Once the rice is ready, fluff it up with a #fork{} and stir in the
@peas{120%grams}, @chipotle paste{20%grams} and @butter{20%grams}.

Pop the lid back on and allow the peas to heat through, ~{1%minute}.

Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Share the chipotle pilaf between your #bowls{} and drizzle over the
@soured cream{75%grams}.

Top with the glazed halloumi to finish. Enjoy!

> Add less chipotle paste if you'd prefer things milder.